1.Wifi is defined on IEEE 802.11 standard.
It functions on the first two OSI layers that is physical and data link layer.
Physical layer defines the frequency bands that is 2.4/5/6 /Ghz ,Modulation techniques(DSS,ODFM) and data rate(54 Mbps,600 Mbps).(Signal transmission)
Data Link Layer defines the MAC addressing, frame formatting,Retransmission etc.(Communication)

