3.
BSS:
*Basic Service Set
*Wifi Network with Single Access Point(AP).
*Multiple Client devices like phone,laptop,TV etc connect to this AP within the network.

ESS:
*Extended Service Set
*Multiple BSS connected together.
*All AP share the same SSID.
*Universities ,airports etc are example locations of ESS.

4.
*Wireless Connectivity
*Authentication:Verifies users
*Data Forwarding:Forwards data between wireless and wired devices
*Network Management:Load balancing,channel selection etc.
*Security:Firewall ,Encryption

5.
Bridge mode connects two networks wirelessly.One AP is connected to another between two different networks maintain high speed.Used to connect two buildings.

Repeater mode has one repeater AP that extends Wifi Coverage client devices through a root AP.In this a router is connected to a repeater.It increases signal range.

6.
• IEEE 802.11a: 54 Mbit/s, 5 GHz standard (1999).Has less interference.
• IEEE 802.11b: 5.5 Mbit/s and 11 Mbit/s,crowded 2.4 GHz standard (1999).Has more interference.

